1) Consistent ecosystem, everything you see here in Webstorm is also possible in other products, such as:
    a) IntelliJ IDEA

    b) PhpStorm

    c) RubyMine

    d) PyCharm


2) Integration with many libraries by default
    a) angular
        autocompletion, directives, navigation

    b) node
        debugging, live console

    c) require
        navigation, refactoring - moving files changes their paths

    d) any other library can be added to libs


3) Integration code visioning systems by default
    a) Mercurial

    b) Git

    c) SVN

    d) Perforce

    e) CVS


4) Full support for modern front-end workflow
    a) grunt
        grunt console

    b) bower
        easy installation, removing, updating
        preferences -> javascript -> bower
        Ctrl + Alt + S -> bower
        Ctrl + Shift + A -> bower


5) Navigation to directories, files, narrowing down search
    a) navigate to file/directory
        Ctrl + Shift + N

    b) navigate to class
        Ctrl + N

    c) navigate to any symbol
        Ctrl + Shift + Alt + N

    d) navigate by clicking symbol
        Ctrl + left mouse click

    e) navigate to method or property
        Ctrl + F12

    f) jQuery navigation to selector (CSS/HTML)
        Ctrl + B


6) Autocompletion
    a) autocomplete everything, everywhere
        f

    b) autocomplete with camelcase
        for example navigation to file

    c) force auto complete
        Ctrl + Space

    d) cyclic completion
        Alt + /


7) Live templates
    us, con, out, met, itar


8) Static code analysis, checks for errors as you type
    a) jsHint

    b) jsLint

    c) GoogleClosures

    d) inspector Hector


9) Multiple cursors
    a) select word, select more Alt+J

    b) Alt + left mouse click

    c) column selection


10) Searching
    a) search in files

    b) search in project, path or scope

    c) regex

    d) search everywhere
        double shift

    e) search in list of directories


11) Emmet, HTML/CSS generator
    a) div.myTest>ul>li*10>lorem

    b) a[href='www.google.ie']	//;-)

    c) w100, h10, dn, db, p0, m0


12) Local history, this can be life saving!


13) Language injections
    a) autocompletes and highlights JS inside HTML and vice versa


14) Refactoring, formatting and code analysis tools


15) Panels, scopes, todos, command line


16) Built spell check


17) Lens mode, useful in long files


18) Optimize selectors, fold/unfold, color picker, color markers


19) Diffs, comparison with CVS, clipboard, other file


20) Help
    a) Up to date documentation
        Menu -> Help -> Help topics

    b) Productivity guide

    c) JetBrainsTV FaceTube Channel
